Acceptance: Room requests reuse existing GitHub-originated runner/work-item semantics for isolation, runner selection, acknowledgement, cancellation, retry, progress, blocked, and completion. Code-changing and constrained PR creation reuse T007; background permission is separate, duplicate keys do not duplicate work, progress/results land in the anchored thread, and receipts plus webhooks reconcile without loops. The P19 pilot-only App-attributed action gate is explicit and off by default outside the named pilot pending P21 migration. Canonical contract: docs/plans/2026-07-12-github-item-room-routing.md.